events.name: Astronomers Spot Object Locked in an Unusual “Dance” with Neptune That Challenges Past Ideas on the Outer Solar System
events.description: In the dark, icy outskirts of our solar system—far beyond Neptune’s orbit—astronomers have discovered a cosmic oddball that appears to be locked in an unusual gravitational dance with the eighth planet.  The object, dubbed 2020 VN40, is the first ever confirmed trans-Neptunian object (TNO) found in a 10:1 mean motion resonance with Neptune.
